				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204880" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;" >DarkStuff</a></span> <span class="odate time_1609274572 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Dec 2020 20:42</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4856866">
									

<p>Sorry, sorry, I just remembered the initials GM and thought &quot;George? George sounds right.&quot; Alright, so, I have a bit more to spill here.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">I&nbsp;put&nbsp;my&nbsp;insecurities&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;box&nbsp;so&nbsp;that&nbsp;they&nbsp;take&nbsp;up&nbsp;less&nbsp;forum&nbsp;space!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">woot</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I was gonna do it in an edit to the author post but&#8230; nah. So, you may remember that I got you for a previous Art Exchange as well. I wasn't going to gift to you again except <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4037075&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609286925" alt="Elogee FishTruck" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4037075)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/elogee-fishtruck" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4037075); return false;">Elogee FishTruck</a></span> and each did one half of the gifter/giftee organization and he forgot that I'd gifted to you so recently. Not a dig at him at all, just not something I would have done, and it was too close to giving people the PMs as to who they were gifting to change things around, so it went through.</p>
<p>But I see it as an opportunity, because there's some stuff I'd like to say, to my writing acquaintance Conwell. When last I gave you a present, it was rather self-serving, as it was 10,000 words of establishing my own GoI, WWS, in the Those Twisted Pines canon. While I do think you liked <a href="/on-the-radar">On the Radar</a>, it launched into some rather unfortunate, and I believe kind of selfish moves on my part. See, I thought that putting WWS in your canon would have been cool and collaborative. And it would have been!</p>
<p>If you liked it.</p>
<p>And, as it turned out, you ended up rather lukewarm on the WWS tale series that I was setting in the Pacific Northwest. The 16 tales I tagged with your canon, the Stories My Dad Told Me tales, were barely relevant to anything in the canon, except that near the end the intersection with Site-64 and connection to On the Radar became clear. And now, they take up a very eyecatching amount of space on your canon's hub.</p>
<p>An amount of space that makes me the second-largest Twisted Pines contributor in terms of article count, and yet I had barely read any of it when I started writing for it. That has been largely remedied now, as I read the majority of the Anderson Robotics arc via researching for this gift, which I kind of see as &quot;making it up to you&quot;. And, using this as a way to open the door for conversation&#8230; would you rather I remove the twisted-pines tag from the first third of the WWS series and remove them from your hub? If you don't think they're adding anything, which is a possibility I have been quietly expecting for a while, I think it'd be best if I simply removed them. And then this, which more directly ties into everything you've so worked to create, can replace it, and I can be an actual contributor to your canon, not just on a technicality but in spirit.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

